details.text: The extension http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/structuredefinition-standards-status is not allowed to be used at this point (this element is [CodeSystem]; allowed for this version = e:Basic, e:CodeSystem.concept, e:StructureDefinition.context, e:SearchParameter.base, e:ElementDefinition, e:ElementDefinition.type, e:ElementDefinition.type.targetProfile, e:OperationDefinition.parameter, e:OperationDefinition.parameter.type, e:OperationDefinition.parameter.targetProfile, e:ImplementationGuide.definition.page)
HL7 Defined CodeSystems SHOULD have a stated value for the caseSensitive element so that users know the status and meaning of the code system clearly
